data.name: Mediterranean Stuffed Peppers
data.quickTastyDescription: Colorful bell peppers filled with a savory mix of quinoa, olives, and feta cheese, perfect for a light meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cook the quinoa according to package instructions and let it cool.
While the quinoa is cooking, slice the tops off the bell peppers and remove the seeds.
In a mixing bowl, combine the cooked quinoa, feta cheese, black olives, cherry tomatoes, olive oil, minced garlic, oregano, salt, and pepper.
Stuff the bell peppers with the quinoa mixture and place them upright in a baking dish.
Add a splash of water to the bottom of the dish to help steam the peppers while cooking.
Cover the baking dish with foil and bake for 25 minutes. Remove the foil and bake for an additional 5 minutes to lightly brown the tops.
Remove from the oven and let cool slightly before serving.
